        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 12:22PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 1221 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Yosemite Valley, or 22 miles north of Yosemite South Entrance, moving
east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Merced Lake High Sierra Camp, Sunrise High Sierra Camp, Tuolumne
Meadows, Little Yosemite Valley Campground, Merced Lake Ranger
Station, Porcupine Flat Campground, Morraine Dome Campground, May
Lake High Sierra Camp, Snow Flat, Vogelsang High Sierra Camp,
Tuolumne High Sierra Camp, Little Yosemite Valley Ranger Station,
Tuolumne Meadows Visitor Center, Yosemite Creek Campground, Tenaya
Lake, Tuolumne Meadows Campground, and Yosemite Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
